Two RTOS tasks

    LED_Task

    Purpose:
        - Updates the WS2814 LED strip based on the most recently received canByte

    Inputs:
        - canByte (updated by CAN receive interupt)

    Function:
        - Reads the most recently received canByte
        - Decode bits (headlights, turn indicators, brake)
        - Populate WS2814 LED data arrays for color and or pattern
        - Update DMA PWM buffer
        - Decide on a time period to run this 



    Send_CAN_Read_ADC_Task

    Purpose:
        - Reads new ADC data from DMA buffer and sends CAN message with updated sensor info
        - We never want to send CAN without having new ADC data so we bundle two processes
            - Only invoke task when
                - ADC is finished converting
                - DMA has written new values into memory
                - ADC DMA interupt signals taks

    Inputs:
        - ADC buffer (populated by DMA)
        - Semaphore given by ADC DMA complete interupt

    Function:
        - Block semaphore until DMA signals conversion completion
        - Read the newly filled ADC buffer from memory
        - Convert/process ADC readings as needed // don't do unecessary processing
            - ADC gives 12-bit values but CAN messages use 8-bit bytes
        - Construct CAN message payload
            - create the actual bytes that go in the CAN frame
        - Send CAN message 
       -  Restart ADC DMA for next conversion cycle`
    